The paper deals with distributed estimation of a Gaussian vector with linear observation model, which is a common problem in information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). The use of digital modulation and power-constrained fading channels suggests a focus on wireless communication (cs.MM) and networked systems (cs.NI). The optimization problems and numerical investigations involve power allocation and performance evaluation, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.MA).
